mbelib
------------------------------------------
mbelib supports the 7200x4400 bit/s codec used in P25 Phase 1, the 7100x4400
bit/s codec used in ProVoice and the 'Half Rate' 3600x2250 bit/s vocoder used
in various radio systems.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libmbe1-1.3.0-1bl2
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.13.1-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/szechyjs/mbelib

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/szechyjs/mbelib/archive/v1.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mbelib-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mbelib-1.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mbelib-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mbelib-1.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmbe1-1.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmbe-devel-1.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mbelib)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mbelib.README
  /usr/share/doc/mbelib/COPYRIGHT
  /usr/share/doc/mbelib/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/mbelib/README.md

(libmbe1)
  /usr/bin/cygmbe-1.dll

(libmbe-devel)
  /usr/include/mbelib.h
  /usr/lib/libmbe.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/mbelib.pc

------------------

